The added CVEs are:

‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë61884 ‚Äì SSRF in Oracle E-Business Suite, remotely exploitable without authentication. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë33073 ‚Äì Improper access control in Windows SMB client, privilege escalation risk. :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë2746 ‚Äì Authentication bypass in Kentico Xperience CMS. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë2747 ‚Äì Another authentication bypass in Kentico Xperience CMS. :contentReference[oaicite:10]{index=10}
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2022‚Äë48503 ‚Äì Validation flaw in Apple‚Äôs JavaScriptCore (historical, but newly tracked). :contentReference[oaicite:12]{index=12}

The four disclosed flaws are:

‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë6541 (CVSS 8.6) ‚Äì OS command injection that can be exploited by an attacker who logs in to the web management interface. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}  
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë6542 (CVSS 9.3) ‚Äì OS command injection exploitable **by a remote unauthenticated attacker**. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}  
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë7850 (CVSS 9.3) ‚Äì OS command injection requiring admin credentials of the web portal. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}  
‚Ä¢ CVE‚Äë2025‚Äë7851 (CVSS 8.7) ‚Äì Improper privilege management vulnerability that may allow root shell under certain conditions. :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}

‚Ä¢ **Upgrade dependencies immediately**: For example, migrate to `astral-tokio-tar` version 0.5.6 or later, which contains the patch. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}  
‚Ä¢ **Audit build/CI pipelines**: Check for usage of async-tar/tokio-tar and nested archive extraction.  
‚Ä¢ **Treat TAR extraction as untrusted input**: Use sandboxing, limit extraction directory permissions, verify archive contents before extraction.  
‚Ä¢ **Use alternate, actively maintained libraries**: Where possible, switch to `tar-rs` or synchronous extraction wrapped in async context. :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}  
‚Ä¢ **Enforce supply-chain hygiene**: Validate packages, manifest contents, and implement image scanning to detect unexpected file additions.

‚Ä¢ The Hacker News ‚Äî "TARmageddon Flaw in Async-Tar Rust Library Could Enable Remote Code Execution" (Oct 22 2025) https://thehackernews.com/2025/10/tarmageddon-flaw-in-async-tar-rust.html  
‚Ä¢ NVD Entry for CVE-2025-62518: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-62518  
‚Ä¢ Security Affairs Report: "TARmageddon flaw in Rust async-tar library allows to smuggle extra archives" (Oct 22 2025) :contentReference[oaicite:10]{index=10}

‚Ä¢ The Hacker News ‚Äì ‚ÄúCritical Lanscope Endpoint Manager Bug Exploited in Ongoing Cyberattacks, CISA Confirms‚Äù (Oct 23 2025) https://thehackernews.com/2025/10/critical-lanscope-endpoint-manager-bug.html  
‚Ä¢ SecurityWeek ‚Äì Lanscope Endpoint Manager Zero-Day Exploited in the Wild. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}  
‚Ä¢ Japan Vulnerability Notes (JVN) / JPCERT/CC advisory confirming customer environments received malicious packets. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}

According to Cisco Talos and reporting by The Hacker News, key aspects of the attack include: 

‚Ä¢ Initial access via **leaked administrative credentials** (VPN or remote access) or spear-phishing & fake CAPTCHA landing pages. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}  
‚Ä¢ Credential theft using tools such as Mimikatz, WebBrowserPassView, and BypassCredGuard. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}  
‚Ä¢ Deployment of legitimate remote management & monitoring tools (AnyDesk via Atera, ScreenConnect, Splashtop) to facilitate lateral movement and persistence. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}  
‚Ä¢ Use of a vulnerable driver (e.g., _eskle.sys_) via BYOVD to disable defenses, kill security processes, and elevate privileges. :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}  
‚Ä¢ Transfer of a Linux ransomware binary to Windows systems (via WinSCP) and execution via Splashtop, allowing encryption across both Windows and Linux hosts in the environment. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}  
‚Ä¢ Targeting backup infrastructure (e.g., Veeam) using credential theft from backup DBs and VSS deletion before encryption. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}
